{"key":"processedPost-17854975","value":{"id":17854975,"first":17853974,"last":17854997,"when":1361679668,"utime":"02/24/13 06:21 AM","content":"Oil heaters are best, but a fact of physics is that a 20F rise in temperature in a sealed room will cut the humidity in half, regardless of the means used to raise the temperature.<br /><br />It's because warm air has more <i>moisture-holding</i> capacity therefore a given amount of humidity in the air at a lower temp will result in a lower RH when the temperature is increased.<br />RR","title":"Re: Heating and humidity!","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}